{"updated_at": "2013-08-12T12:59:31Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2013-08-12T12:59:20Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/22491152", "id": 22491152, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11850", "issue_id": 11850, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/razielgn", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "f8990e1991980f60be9ab371a214a21d", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f8990e1991980f60be9ab371a214a21d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F754d4f6ffc6d68670cd24ba3eda27e63.png", "id": 237493, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/events{/privacy}", "login": "razielgn", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/razielgn/followers"}, "body": ">Thanks. The current solution seems to be prone for false positives though. Maybe we could rescue and use respond_to? to check if it is avaialble or not, instead of relying on stacktraces?\r\n\r\nSpent some more time on it and managed to remove backtraces completely by using `NoMethodError#name`\u001c, which carries the not found method. :smile: ", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d0afbd3543c151007d0d"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11850#issuecomment-22491152"}
